
# VEGA SC317 - Robot Control Libraries

This directory contains all the control libraries for the VEGA SC317 autonomous wheeled robot.

## Directory Structure

```
lib/
├── Communication/     # NRF24L01 wireless communication
├── Control/          # Hardware actuators (servos, motors)
├── EKF/             # Extended Kalman Filter for state estimation
├── Navigation/      # Main navigation controller and state machine
├── Pathfinding/     # Path following and kinematics algorithms
├── Sensors/         # Obstacle detection and precision sensors
└── README          # This file
```

## Library Overview

### Communication
- NRF24L01 radio communication with ground station
- Multi-format data reception (strings, floats, raw data)
- Bidirectional communication with acknowledgments

### Control
- Hardware actuator management
- 4 servo motors for 4-wheel steering (PCA9685)
- 6 stepper motors for propulsion (TMC2208)
- Safety systems and motor control

### EKF (Extended Kalman Filter)
- State estimation combining IMU and odometry
- Position, velocity, and orientation tracking
- Sensor fusion for accurate localization

### Navigation
- Main navigation controller integrating all subsystems
- State machine for mission management
- Real-time navigation with obstacle avoidance

### Pathfinding
- A* path following algorithm
- Instantaneous Center of Rotation (ICR) kinematics
- 4-wheel steering control calculations

### Sensors
- 4x VL53L3CX ToF sensors for obstacle detection
- IR docking sensor for precision target approach
- Emergency stop and safety monitoring

## Dependencies

The following libraries are required (configured in `platformio.ini`):

- `TMCStepper` - Stepper motor control
- `Adafruit_PWMServoDriver` - Servo control
- `VL53L3CX` - Time-of-flight sensors
- `esp-idf-mirf` - NRF24L01 communication

## Usage

Include the libraries in your code:

```cpp
#include "Navigation/Navigation.h"      // Main controller
#include "Communication/NRF.h"         // Radio communication
#include "Control/HardwareControl.h"   // Actuators
#include "Sensors/Detection.h"         // Obstacle detection
```

## Integration

The system is designed with a modular architecture where each subsystem can be tested and developed independently while working together through the main `NavigationController` class.

For detailed API documentation, see the README files in each subdirectory.
